step_data.thought:
I've been comparing different map styles to find the one with the most detail for urban areas. I've examined all four available styles (Standard, CyclOSM, ÖPNVKarte, and Humanitarian) and have zoomed in three times to get a better view of urban details.

I'm currently viewing the Humanitarian style. To complete my comparison, I should look at each style at this zoom level to determine which one shows the most urban detail. Let me switch back to the Standard style first to compare it with the current Humanitarian style.

To access the layer menu again, I need to click on the 'Layers' button (bid 414).
